Package org.jmisb.api.klv.st1201

Class DecodeResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jmisb.api.klv.st1201.DecodeResult
  • public class DecodeResult
extends Object
    Container class for the result of an ST1201 decode operation.

    This holds the kind of value mapping, and the results, which is either a double value for a normal mapped value, or an unsigned long identifier for the special cases.

    • Method Detail

      • getKind

        public ValueMappingKind getKind()
        The kind of result.

        This can be thought of as a namespace, and indicates how to interpret the rest of the result. For ValueMappingKind.NormalMappedValue, the result value is provided by getValue(). For other kinds of results, the result value is provided by getIdentifier() if applicable.

        Returns:
        the kind of result

      • setKind

        public void setKind​(ValueMappingKind kind)
        Set the kind of result.

        This can be thought of as a namespace, and indicates how to interpret the rest of the result. For ValueMappingKind.NormalMappedValue, the result value is set by setValue(double). For other kinds of results, the result value is set by setIdentifier(long) if applicable.

        Parameters:
        kind - the kind of result

      • getIdentifier

        public long getIdentifier()
        Get the special-case identifier value.

        This is the value associated with one of the special-case kinds of value (that is, something other than ValueMappingKind.NormalMappedValue. Some kinds of values (for example, ValueMappingKind.PositiveInfinity only ever have a value of 0, but others can have signaling identifiers included. For example, ValueMappingKind.UserDefined allows use of identifiers to indicate which specific user defined identifier is meant.

        Returns:
        the identifier for the special case kind.

      • setIdentifier

        public void setIdentifier​(long identifier)
        Set the special-case identifier value.

        This is the value associated with one of the special-case kinds of value (that is, something other than ValueMappingKind.NormalMappedValue. Some kinds of values (for example, ValueMappingKind.PositiveInfinity only ever have a value of 0, but others can have signaling identifiers included. For example, ValueMappingKind.UserDefined allows use of identifiers to indicate which specific user defined identifier is meant.

        Parameters:
        identifier - the identifier for the special case kind.

      • getValue

        public double getValue()
        Get the normal mapped value.

        This is the value associated with the ValueMappingKind.NormalMappedValue decode result, which is the common-case for ST1201 decoding.

        Returns:
        the decoded value as a double.
